:: about [nobr]
<main>
<h1>About</h1>
<p>Letters from us is a community storytelling project that invites people in Islington to tell the story of their area, in their own words. Inspired by the long-running BBC radio show Letter from America, the project invites residents from different ages and backgrounds to share their stories and reflect on how they see their community.</p>
 
<p>Creative team:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Creative director: Marie Klimis</li>
  <li>Live journalist: Glenda Cooper</li>
  <li>Illustrator: Jess Sanders</li>
  <li>Creative programmer: Suzanna Hurst</li>
</ul>

<p>Letters from us is a project from Koro Productions, an arts charity based in Islington. </p>

<p>To support our work, sign up for our <a href="https://www.koro.org.uk/contact" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">newsletter</a>, follow us on <a href="https://www.instagram.com/koroproductions_" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Instagram</a> or <a href="https://www.justgiving.com/charity/koroproductionsltd" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">donate</a> to keep our growing archive alive. </p>
<<button "Back to Map">>
  <<goto "map">>
  <</button>>
</main>


